      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Colleen Kollar-Kotelly",
      "uco-core:description": "District Judge, District of Columbia; presides over 1:24-cr-00417-CKK; took the nine guilty pleas and imposed the Desmond, Tangeman, and Ferro sentences. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), assignment and minute entries"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:e54ecd62-9da3-59fb-8d04-f9029e7e8898",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Malone Lam",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 1, also known as 'King Greavys', '$$$', '7', 'Kg', and 'Anne Hathaway'. Charged organizer and target identifier of the SE Enterprise; participant in the Victim-7 theft of approximately $245,093,239 on 2024-08-19; spent over $4,000,000 in stolen virtual currency at Los Angeles nightclubs between 2024-08-19 and 2024-09-10; tossed his mobile telephone into Biscayne Bay on 2024-09-18 after learning agents were coming to arrest him. Arrested in Miami, Florida on 2024-09-18 on a warrant dated 2024-09-17. Pending counts 1ss, 2ss, 3ss (plus earlier-instrument counts) as of the docket printout. Source: PACER Doc 245 (redacted; unredacted Doc 229 returned 2025-10-29) (indictment_ss), caption; paras. 29; overt acts uu-vv, yy, qqqq; Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (1); arrest entries"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:5785af89-575a-56f2-a1fe-3695f9733d2f",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Jeandiel Serrano",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 2, also known as '@SKIDSTAR' and 'VERSACEGOD'. Charged in the original sealed indictment (Doc 1) with conspiracy to commit wire fraud and money laundering; identified in the Tangeman statement of offense as an SE Enterprise member for whom Tangeman procured the 'Hesby House' Los Angeles rental under a fake identity. Arrested in Los Angeles, California on 2024-09-18. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (2); arrest entries; Source: PACER Doc 257 (soo), Hesby House facts"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:de9db80f-e123-5283-952d-5e86dc8b2e24",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Marlon Ferro",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 3, also known as 'Marlo' and 'GothFerrari'. Arrested in California on 2025-05-13; pleaded guilty to Count 1 (RICO conspiracy) on 2025-10-17 and was sentenced on 2026-05-06 to 78 months' incarceration followed by 36 months' supervised release and a $100 special assessment; Counts 2 and 3 dismissed on the government's oral motion. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (3); plea and sentencing minute entries"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:0a47f7c5-9070-56d9-b53b-73adb439da7e",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Hamza Doost",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 4, also known as 'Scyllia'. Arrested in California on 2025-05-13; pleaded guilty to Count 1 (RICO conspiracy) on 2025-08-25. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (4); plea minute entry"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:ecfa9b88-7c87-551e-a72f-0ce6160cfb2a",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Conor Flansburg",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 5, also known as 'OO', 'Green Room', and '@D0UU0B'. Charged database hacker/organizer designated COCONSPIRATOR C.F. in later instruments; named in the Tangeman statement of offense (as 'Connor Flansburg') among the SE Enterprise members who arrived in Los Angeles. Arrested in California on 2025-05-13; pleaded guilty to Count 1 (RICO conspiracy) on 2025-09-26. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (5); plea minute entry; Source: PACER Doc 257 (soo), Statement of Facts"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:27d4771a-76b9-5df8-aa63-4c29dcd223ce",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Kunal Mehta",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 6, also known as 'Papa', 'The Accountant', 'Shrek', and 'Neil'. Charged money launderer for the SE Enterprise. Arrested in California on 2025-05-13; pleaded guilty to Count 1ss (RICO conspiracy, Second Superseding Indictment) on 2025-11-17. Source: PACER Doc 245 (redacted; unredacted Doc 229 returned 2025-10-29) (indictment_ss), para. 31; Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (6); plea minute entry"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:aa7560a1-ceab-574c-b086-aaa199d1a35c",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Ethan Yarally",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 7, also known as 'Rand' and '15%'. Charged caller for the SE Enterprise. Arrested in Sterling, Virginia on 2025-07-25; pleaded guilty to Count 1s (RICO conspiracy) on 2026-01-08. Source: PACER Doc 245 (redacted; unredacted Doc 229 returned 2025-10-29) (indictment_ss), para. 30; Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (7); plea minute entry"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:42fc43db-1d3d-5bcb-b363-ad56d85aff00",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Cody Demirtas",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 8, also known as 'KO' and 'Kody'. Arrested in Dulles, Virginia on 2025-07-16; pleaded guilty to Count 1 (RICO conspiracy) on 2025-10-14. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (8); plea minute entry"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:690a9198-02c3-57cd-b479-63af6b7dc9ff",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Aakaash Anand",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 9, also known as 'Light' and 'Dark'. Charged caller and money launderer for the SE Enterprise; assisted with laundering the Victim-7 proceeds on no-KYC exchanges and traveled from New Zealand in September 2024 to retrieve luxury clothing purchased with stolen virtual currency. Counts 1s, 2s, 3s pending. Source: PACER Doc 245 (redacted; unredacted Doc 229 returned 2025-10-29) (indictment_ss), paras. 30-31; overt acts xx, lll; Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (9)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:ee9929a5-4779-5303-9c4f-7c0d7802af40",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Evan Tangeman",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 10, also known as 'Tate', 'E', and 'Evan | Exchanger'. Money launderer for the SE Enterprise who provided unlicensed crypto-to-cash services (typically at a 7% commission), procured rental mansions under fake identities for enterprise members, watched the 2024-09-18 FBI searches of Lam's Miami homes through remote security-camera access, and directed co-defendant Tucker Desmond to destroy co-conspirators' digital devices after the Lam and Serrano arrests. Arrested in California on 2025-05-13; pleaded guilty to Count One of the Second Superseding Indictment (RICO conspiracy; minute-entry label Count 1ss) on 2025-12-08; sentenced on 2026-04-24 to 70 months' incarceration followed by 36 months' supervised release and a $100 special assessment; the money-laundering conspiracy count (3ss) was dismissed on the government's oral motion. The docket header lists his terminated counts as 1, 3, and 3s. Source: PACER Doc 257 (soo), Summary of the Plea Agreement; Statement of Facts; Source: PACER Doc 318 (sentmemo), passim; Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (10); plea and sentencing minute entries"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:89e72b58-fd01-59dc-a806-39c0bd7eb00b",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Joel Cortes",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 11, also known as 'J'. Arrested in California on 2025-05-13; pleaded guilty to Count 1 (RICO conspiracy) on 2025-07-31 \u2014 the first defendant to plead. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (11); plea minute entry"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:ae9abe7f-0470-5c6d-a8ba-2dc9bd4109d7",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "FNU LNU-1",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 12, name unknown, also known as '~_~', 'Squiggly', and 'CHEN'. Charged database hacker for the SE Enterprise; participant in the Victim-7 theft. Counts 1s and 2s pending. Source: PACER Doc 245 (redacted; unredacted Doc 229 returned 2025-10-29) (indictment_ss), para. 28; overt acts uu-vv; Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (12)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:01106522-6bc1-5adb-ac6d-9ff1b27ab641",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "FNU LNU-2",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 13, name unknown, also known as 'Danny' and 'Meech'. Counts 1, 2, and 3 of the Superseding Indictment pending. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (13)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:8956d4ca-4f85-5f33-9a74-c8feb8a643e9",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Tucker Desmond",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 14. At Tangeman's direction after the Lam and Serrano arrests, traveled to Lam's Los Angeles homes, retrieved electronic devices, and destroyed them to prevent their seizure by law enforcement. Arrested in California on 2025-05-13; pleaded guilty to Count 4 (obstruction of justice) on 2025-10-15 and was sentenced on 2026-03-20 to 36 months' probation and a $100 special assessment; Count 3 dismissed. Source: PACER Doc 318 (sentmemo), introduction; Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (14); plea and sentencing minute entries"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:63c8bc2a-9eaf-5a8d-b1ba-2fd2fe107f73",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Danish Zulfiqar",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 15, also known as 'Danish Khan', 'Danny', 'W.', and 'Meech'. Added in the Second Superseding Indictment; Counts 1, 2, and 3 pending. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (15)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:b7929da9-0ec2-5d2e-a0a7-16ca8a002196",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Mustafa Ibrahim",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 16, also known as 'Krust' and 'KRR'. Added in the Second Superseding Indictment; Counts 1, 2, and 3 pending. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (16)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:5da6113c-5674-54fc-ac57-80e4140d00f2",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Nicolas Dellecave",
      "uco-core:description": "Defendant 17, also known as 'Nic' and 'Souja'. Added in the Second Superseding Indictment; Counts 1, 2, and 3 pending. Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), Defendant (17)"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:04fd1056-9078-5f59-9969-fc066c494e55",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "COCONSPIRATOR M.F.",
      "uco-core:description": "Unnamed co-conspirator designated by initials in the Second Superseding Indictment; served as the SE Enterprise's residential burglar / IRL break-in member. In July 2024 flew to New Mexico, set up a telephone with a video camera across from Victim-4's home to livestream the break-in, and on 2024-07-08, in coordination with Lam and others, broke into Victim-4's home in search of hardware virtual currency devices. The identity behind the initials is not established in the reviewed documents. Source: PACER Doc 245 (redacted; unredacted Doc 229 returned 2025-10-29) (indictment_ss), para. 32; overt acts kk-mm"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:b112d3db-75ad-505c-a2ca-397b14dfbc42",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "MONEY EXCHANGER-1",
      "uco-core:description": "Unnamed unlicensed crypto-to-cash money transmitter designated in the charging documents; with Tangeman, laundered approximately $3,000,000 in cryptocurrency for Lam on 2024-08-25/26 so Lam could obtain a new Los Angeles rental home, instructing Lam to send $550,000 tranches in USDT and deducting from the total owed each time. Source: PACER Doc 245 (redacted; unredacted Doc 229 returned 2025-10-29) (indictment_ss), overt act aaa; Source: PACER Doc 318 (sentmemo), Statement of Facts quotes"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:f9319dac-9c51-54aa-8f36-fc323e207f4c",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Victim-4",
      "uco-core:description": "Victim identified only as Victim-4. Target of a social-engineering fraud scheme; Lam accessed Victim-4's Apple iCloud account in July 2024 to monitor Victim-4's location in real time, and COCONSPIRATOR M.F. broke into Victim-4's New Mexico home on 2024-07-08 in search of hardware virtual currency devices. Source: PACER Doc 245 (redacted; unredacted Doc 229 returned 2025-10-29) (indictment_ss), overt acts ii-mm"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:8924702a-2e7b-5a74-8c9f-14dc0ef6aa9b",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Person",
      "uco-core:name": "Victim-7",
      "uco-core:description": "Victim identified only as Victim-7. On 2024-08-19, while at his home in Washington, D.C., was convinced by Lam, COCONSPIRATOR-1, COCONSPIRATOR-2, CHEN, and another to download a remote desktop connection program; the conspirators accessed his computer and stole approximately $245,093,239.00 in virtual currency \u2014 the largest single theft charged. Source: PACER Doc 245 (redacted; unredacted Doc 229 returned 2025-10-29) (indictment_ss), overt acts uu-vv"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:a05ac64c-6cca-5a4a-b7bf-a75444f4ffff",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Organization",
      "uco-core:name": "U.S. Attorney's Office for the District of Columbia",
      "uco-core:description": "Prosecuting office. The government's Tangeman sentencing memorandum is submitted by U.S. Attorney Jeanine Ferris Pirro; AUSAs of record across the docket include Kevin L. Rosenberg and William G. Hart. Source: PACER Doc 318 (sentmemo), signature block; Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), minute entries"
    },
    {
      "@id": "urn:uuid:04f62c49-3693-5552-b6c7-03ad418ce827",
      "@type": "uco-identity:Organization",
      "uco-core:name": "Federal Bureau of Investigation",
      "uco-core:description": "Investigating agency; executed the 2024-09-18 search warrants at Lam's two Miami rental homes (watched remotely by Tangeman through the security camera system) and the 2025-05-13 arrests in California. Source: PACER Doc 318 (sentmemo), Statement of Facts; Source: PACER Doc docket sheet (docket), arrest entries"
    },
